"Orkin V.L., Guschin A.G., Larin I.K., Huie R.E., Kurylo M.J.","Measurement of the infrared absorption cross-sections of haloalkanes and their use in a simplified calculational approach for estimating direct global warming potentials",2003,"Journal of Photochemistry and Photobiology A: Chemistry","157","2-3",,"211","222",,,10.1016/S1010-6030(03)00057-1,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0037420828&partnerID=40&md5=44b7b316bcaa724352db4b2a06c82e78","Inst. Energy Problems Chem. Phys., Russian Academy of Sciences, Leninsky Prospect 38, Bldg. 2, Moscow 117829, Russian Federation; Physical/Chemical Properties Div., Natl. Inst. of Standards/Technology, Gaithersburg, MD 20899, United States","Orkin, V.L., Inst. Energy Problems Chem. Phys., Russian Academy of Sciences, Leninsky Prospect 38, Bldg. 2, Moscow 117829, Russian Federation, Physical/Chemical Properties Div., Natl. Inst. of Standards/Technology, Gaithersburg, MD 20899, United States; Guschin, A.G., Inst. Energy Problems Chem. Phys., Russian Academy of Sciences, Leninsky Prospect 38, Bldg. 2, Moscow 117829, Russian Federation; Larin, I.K., Inst. Energy Problems Chem. Phys., Russian Academy of Sciences, Leninsky Prospect 38, Bldg. 2, Moscow 117829, Russian Federation; Huie, R.E., Physical/Chemical Properties Div., Natl. Inst. of Standards/Technology, Gaithersburg, MD 20899, United States; Kurylo, M.J., Physical/Chemical Properties Div., Natl. Inst. of Standards/Technology, Gaithersburg, MD 20899, United States","The infrared absorption cross-sections and integrated band intensities (IBIs) for 21 haloalkanes: CFCl3, CF2Cl2, CF2Br2, CH2F2, CHF2Cl, CHF2Br, CF3Br, CHCl2-CF2Cl, CHFCl-CFCl2, CHCl2-CF3, CHClBr-CF3, CHFCl-CF2Cl, CHFBr-CF3, CHF2-CF3, CH2Br-CF3, CH2F-CFCl2, CH2F-CF3, CH3-CCl3, CH3-CFCl2, CH3-CF2-CF3, and CHF2-CH 2-CF3 were measured over the wavenumber range 400-1600 cm-1 at T = 295 K. The effect of air pressure on measured spectra was also investigated. These results are used to demonstrate a simple calculational approach for estimating the direct global warming potentials (GWPs) of such chemicals. The results obtained are compared with those derived from more comprehensive atmospheric modeling calculations appearing in the literature. © 2003 Elsevier Science B.V. All rights reserved.","CFC; Global warming potential; Halon; Infrared absorption cross-sections; Infrared forcing; Pressure broadening","alkane derivative; bromine derivative; bromodifluoromethane; bromotrifluoromethane; chlorodifluoromethane; chlorofluorocarbon; dibromodifluoromethane; dichlorodifluoromethane; difluoromethane; fluorocarbon; halide; trichlorofluoromethane; unclassified drug; atmospheric pressure; atmospheric radioactivity; calculation; controlled study; greenhouse effect; infrared radiation; mathematical model; measurement; radiation absorption; review; scientific literature; spectrophotometry",,"bromotrifluoromethane, 75-63-8; chlorodifluoromethane, 75-45-6; dichlorodifluoromethane, 75-71-8; fluorocarbon, 11072-16-5; trichlorofluoromethane, 75-69-4",,,,"Fisher, D.A., Hales, C.H., Wang, W.-C., Ko, M.K.W., Sze, N.D., (1990) Nature, 344, pp. 513-516; Houghton, J.T., Jenkins, G.J., Ephraums, J.J., (1990) Climate Change: The IPCC Scientific Assessment, Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change (IPCC), , (Eds.), Cambridge University Press, Cambridge, UK; Prinn, R.G., Weiss, R.F., Miller, B.R., Huang, J., Alyea, F.N., Cunnold, D.M., Fraser, P.J., Simmonds, P.G., (1995) Science, 269, pp. 187-192; Prather, M., Spivakovsky, C.M., (1990) J. Geophys. Res., 95, pp. 18723-18729; Spivakovsky, C.M., Logan, J.A., Montzka, S.A., Balkanski, Y.J., Foreman-Fowler, M., Jones, D.B.A., Horowitz, L.W., McElroy, M.B., (2000) J. Geophys. Res., 105, pp. 8931-8980; Orkin, V.L., Khamaganov, V.G., Guschin, A.G., Kasimovskaya, E.E., Larin, I.K., Development of atmospheric characteristics of chlorine-free alternative fluorocarbons (1993), Report on R-134a and E-143a, Report ORNL/Sub/86X-SL103V prepared for th